en_586894_0	The Inter University Bhikkhu Federation held a protest today demanding the shut down of SAITM – the private medical college.
en_586894_1	And just like every other time, it was the public who had to bear the brunt of it, being inconvenienced by the ongoing activities However, the protest was met with tear gas and water cannons, courtesy of Police.
en_586894_2	Why? because the protesters were in violation of a court order by entering Lotus Road.
en_586894_3	The crowd then continued their protest at the Ceramic junction – and yet again, they were greeted with tear gas and dispersed.
en_586894_4	Those who assembled opposite the Fort Railway Station shared the same fate.
en_586894_5	The protesters also charged of a slash in the intake of student bhikkhus to state universities.
en_586894_6	These events provoke the question – Are all these individuals clad in robes ‘members of the venerable clergy’ or mere pretenders?
en_586894_7	If these individuals are pretenders – shouldn’t steps be taken to root them out for the benefit of the Buddha Sasana?
en_586894_8	Even if those who are clad in robes are real members of the clergy, doesn’t their behaviour tarnish the sanctity of the robe?
